      "comment": "A wide draw poses a more off a challenge for SOHO GUNSLINGER (10) but he is in fine form, leading to cruise home by nearly 12m last start. That gave him two wins and a second from his last three outings and took his strike rate here to 50 per cent. Up in distance but is going well enough to overcome the barrier. VITE MONET (6) progressed off a fresh placing over a mile here to win from a wide barrier last start at Bathurst. Owns a good record at the distance and should be at his peak. LAYDEN (2) is up in grade but is suited up to a distance where he has won his two attempts, both of them here. Continues to perform strongly and draws well. COASTAL DRIVE (4) has had seven weeks off since winning here but was kept up to the mark with a trial and is another that will enjoy this longer journey having recorded two wins and a placing from his three attempts. FORCE FULL (9) draws wide but is going well and backs up after making it back-to-back wins by scoring here on Tuesday.",
